Biography

2023-24 HIGHLIGHTS (GRADUATE):

Named to the All-Atlantic 10 Defensive Team

Started all 32 games for VCU and averaged 27.0 minutes per game

Lead team in rebounding at 8.4 per game and averaged 5.3 points

Served as team captain

Recorded a double-double with 11 points and 10 rebounds at Saint Louis (2/7)

Grabbed a career-high 15 rebounds at La Salle (2/24)

2022-23 HIGHLIGHTS (SENIOR):

Appeared in 26 games with 17 starts, missed first three games recovering from injury

Averaged 3.2 points and 5.1 rebounds per game

Led team in both rebounds per game and blocks (19)

Fourth on the team in minutes per game

2021-22 HIGHLIGHTS (JUNIOR):

Appeared in two games, missed remainder of season due to injury

Averaged 0.5 points, 8.5 rebounds and 17.5 minutes in those two games

Grabbed career-high 14 rebounds against Middle Tennessee

PRIOR TO VCU (CREIGHTON):

Started and played in 17 contests for the Blue Jays in 2020-21 as a sophomore

Averaged 1.2 points and 3.2 rebounds per game while playing 12.4 minutes per contest

Parham played in 47 games for Creighton during her two seasons

Averaged 1.6 points and 2.9 rebounds as a freshman in 30 total appearances

HIGH SCHOOL:

A two-time All-South Suburban Conference choice and was named All-State Honorable Mention

Served as team captain and during her senior season had 150 blocks along with 251 rebounds
